                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                            text="&lt;p>AbbVie is an equal opportunity employer. AbbVie does not discriminate based on any legally protected status. As a federal contractor, AbbVie takes affirmative action to employ and advance in employment qualified protected veterans and individuals with a disability. If you are a U.S. or Puerto Rico employee or candidate that would like to view a copy of the nonconfidential portions of the company’s affirmative action plans for Protected Veterans or Individuals with a Disability, or our EEO/Affirmative Action policy statement, please email&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;alentacquisition@abbvie.com&quot;>talentacquisition@abbvie.com&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Employee Polygraph Protection Act, Family Medical Leave Act and Know Your Rights (&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/content/dam/abbvie-com2/pdfs/joinus/eeo/FEDAPP-english.pdf&quot;>English&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;) (&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/content/dam/abbvie-com2/pdfs/joinus/eeo/FEDAPP-spanish.pdf&quot;>Spanish&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;)&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;"
